4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would create the Home Schooling
6 Opportunities for Military Education (HOME) Act.
7 This bill would apply to parents who are active
8 duty members of the Armed Forces of the United States
9 or members of the National Guard or reserve components
10 of the Armed Forces of the United States, and are on
11 active duty orders that require a temporary or
12 permanent change of station.
13 This bill would require those military parents
14 to inform their local superintendent of education of
15 any intention to home school their dependent children
16 and to comply with state law relating to home
17 schooling.
18 This bill would allow dependents of those
19 military parents who are receiving home school
20 instruction to use public school facilities and
21 equipment on the same basis as regularly enrolled
22 students under certain circumstances.
23 This bill would require local school systems to
24 provide home school students with disabilities who are
25 dependents of those military parents and are residing
26 within the system access to special education services.
27 This bill would also require local school
28 systems to allow participation in interscholastic
Page 1

systems to allow participation in interscholastic
SB191 INTRODUCED
29 activities by home school students and other dependents
30 of those military parents residing within the system.
31
