113 1975, is amended to read as follows:
114 "§16-1-52.1
115 (a) For the purposes of this section, the term
116 "athletic association" means any following terms have the
117 following meanings:
118 (1) ATHLETIC ASSOCIATION. Any athletic organization
119 operating in this state that has authority over its member
120 institutions' athletic programs, that receives public funds in
121 any form, and whose member institutions make use of public
122 facilities.
123 (2) BONA FIDE CHANGE IN DUTY STATION OR RESIDENCE. A
124 required relocation pursuant to military orders, whether
125 temporary or permanent, that necessitates the service member
126 to obtain lodging outside the normal commuting area of the
127 member's principal residence.
128 (3) COVERED MILITARY SERVICE. Active duty military
129 service by a member of the Armed Forces of the United States,
130 including a member of the reserve components or the Alabama
131 National Guard, who is:
132 a. Serving on active duty under federal authority; or
133 b. Serving on active duty under state authority
134 pursuant to an order of the Governor or other lawful state
135 authority, when the service requires a bona fide change in
136 duty station or residence.
137 (b)(1) No public K-12 school may deny a dependent child
138 of a full-time active duty military parent immediate
139 eligibility to participate in an interscholastic athletic
140 contest on the basis of the child enrolling in a new school
Page 5

contest on the basis of the child enrolling in a new school
