141 due to the child and his or her parent making a bona fide move
142 pursuant to permanent change of station orders received by the
143 parent, regardless of the date upon which the child enrolls in
144 the new school within the school attendance zone of the bona
145 fide move.
146 (2) A public K-12 school and an athletic association
147 may require a parent to provide his or her permanent change of
148 station orders to substantiate a bona fide move that
149 necessitates a child's enrollment in a new school.
150 (c) No local school system or athletic association may
151 deny a high school equivalency student, a home school student,
152 or a charter school student, whose parent is a member of the
153 Armed Forces of the United States performing covered military
154 service, and who does not have access to interscholastic
155 activities, the opportunity to participate in all
156 interscholastic activities available in the school system
157 within which the student resides, if the student otherwise
158 satisfies all other requirements of the local school system
159 and athletic association, with the exception of class
160 attendance requirements."
161 Section 4. This act shall become effective on July 1,
162 2026.
